  "texts": [
    "(1)The assumption is that the NP-classifier learns the density ratio.",
    "For a good generative model and an optimal classifier, the weight distribution will typically peak near one, with tails to the left (w ≪ 1) and right (w ≫ 1), corresponding to regions of phase space where the generative model is overproducing and underproducing the reference data, respectively.",
    "On general grounds, the NP classifier should have an excess of generated events as a small-weights tail of the distribution, and an excess of reference events as a large-weight tail.",
    "Indeed this is a general pattern we will observe in the different examples we consider in this work.",
    "Having it the other way around, an excess of true events on the left tail and an excess of generated events on the right, would generate a ROC curve below the diagonal, indicating an anti-classifier."
